    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've researched and written:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: `extensions/pulseboard/` — 7 new files, nothing modified\n\n### Key findings from reading the codebase\n\n1. **`getChatChannelMeta` cannot be used for \"pulseboard\"** — it's strictly typed to a closed union of registered `ChatChannelId` values (`src/channels/chat-meta.ts:126`). Calling it with \"pulseboard\" would be a TypeScript error and return `undefined` at runtime. **Fix: construct `ChannelMeta` as a plain object directly** (exactly as IRC does when it spreads the result — we just skip that call and own the object).\n\n2. **`PluginRuntime` is re-exported from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/runtime-store`** — so `runtime.ts` can import both `createPluginRuntimeStore` and `PluginRuntime` from the same path; no local `api.ts` barrel needed.\n\n3. **`outbound.sendText` lives under `outbound.attachedResults`** inside `createChatChannelPlugin` — this is the pattern IRC uses for `sendText`/`sendMedia`, and it's what returns `{ channel, to, messageId }`.\n\n### The 7 files\n\n| File | Pattern source |\n|---|---|\n| `extensions/pulseboard/package.json` | IRC's package.json structure |\n| `extensions/pulseboard/openclaw.plugin.json` | IRC's manifest (id, channels, configSchema) |\n| `extensions/pulseboard/src/types.ts` | 3 plain TS interfaces, no imports |\n| `extensions/pulseboard/src/runtime.ts` | `createPluginRuntimeStore<PluginRuntime>` → `get/setPulseBoardRuntime` |\n| `extensions/pulseboard/src/channel.ts` | `createChatChannelPlugin` with direct+group caps, all stubs |\n| `extensions/pulseboard/index.ts` | `defineChannelPluginEntry` mirroring IRC exactly |\n| `extensions/pulseboard/setup-entry.ts` | `defineSetupPluginEntry(pulseBoardPlugin)` |\n\n### Verification\n- `pnpm tsgo` — type-check all new files\n- `pnpm check` — lint\n- All imports stay within `openclaw/plugin-sdk/*` and package-local paths (boundary compliant)",
